The paper deals with circuit complexity theory and lower bounds, which are typically studied in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial properties and pseudorandomness, which are relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. Information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) are also mentioned in the paper, as they relate to the pseudorandomness assumption used in the main result.
